The article discusses the action plan of the Nuclear Security Summit 2016 in support of the International Criminal Police Organization (INTERPOL). INTERPOL plays a crucial role in countering terrorist and criminal offenses related to nuclear and radioactive material. The plan outlines various actions to enhance information sharing, support investigations and operations, and build capacity. It advocates for INTERPOL to collaborate with other international organizations and initiatives, provide assistance to member countries, and develop training resources and guidance. The plan also emphasizes the need for funding and resources to support INTERPOL's programs and activities.